This paper deals with backdoor attacks on deep neural networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves optimization techniques for creating covert triggers, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The datasets used in the experiments are related to computer vision (cs.CV), and the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed attacks on various DNN models, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the invisibility of the backdoors, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
